.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Marketplace \- NIP\-15 Nostr Marketplace
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Marketplace;
\&
\&    # Create a stall (kind 30017)
\&    my $stall = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->stall_event(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id       => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name     => \*(AqMy Stall\*(Aq,
\&        currency => \*(AqUSD\*(Aq,
\&        shipping => [
\&            { id => \*(Aqzone\-1\*(Aq, name => \*(AqUS\*(Aq, cost => 5.0, regions => [\*(AqUS\*(Aq, \*(AqCA\*(Aq] },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create a product (kind 30018)
\&    my $product = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->product_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id         => \*(Aqprod\-1\*(Aq,
\&        stall_id   => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name       => \*(AqWidget\*(Aq,
\&        currency   => \*(AqUSD\*(Aq,
\&        price      => 10.50,
\&        quantity   => 100,
\&        categories => [\*(Aqelectronics\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create a marketplace (kind 30019)
\&    my $market = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->marketplace_event(
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id        => \*(Aqmarket\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name      => \*(AqMy Market\*(Aq,
\&        merchants => [$merchant_pubkey],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create an auction (kind 30020)
\&    my $auction = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->auction_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id           => \*(Aqauction\-1\*(Aq,
\&        stall_id     => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name         => \*(AqRare Item\*(Aq,
\&        starting_bid => 1000,
\&        duration     => 86400,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Place a bid (kind 1021)
\&    my $bid = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->bid_event(
\&        pubkey           => $hex_pubkey,
\&        amount           => 1500,
\&        auction_event_id => $auction_event_id,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Confirm a bid (kind 1022)
\&    my $confirm = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->bid_confirmation_event(
\&        pubkey           => $hex_pubkey,
\&        bid_event_id     => $bid_event_id,
\&        auction_event_id => $auction_event_id,
\&        status           => \*(Aqaccepted\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Checkout messages (JSON for NIP\-04 direct messages)
\&    my $order = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->order_message(
\&        id          => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        items       => [{ product_id => \*(Aqprod\-1\*(Aq, quantity => 2 }],
\&        shipping_id => \*(Aqzone\-1\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    my $payment = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->payment_request_message(
\&        id              => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        payment_options => [{ type => \*(Aqln\*(Aq, link => \*(Aqlnbc...\*(Aq }],
\&    );
\&
\&    my $status = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->order_status_message(
\&        id      => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        message => \*(AqShipped!\*(Aq,
\&        paid    => JSON::true,
\&        shipped => JSON::true,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse events
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Parse checkout messages
\&    my $checkout = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->parse_checkout_message($json_string);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-15 Nostr Marketplace. Merchants publish stalls, products,
and auctions as Nostr events. Customers interact through bids and checkout
messages sent via NIP\-04 direct messages.
.PP
Six event kinds are involved:
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 30017\fR \- Stall (addressable). Contains stall name, currency, and shipping zones. The ""d"" tag MUST match the stall ""id""." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 30017\fR \- Stall (addressable). Contains stall name, currency, and shipping zones. The \f(CWd\fR tag MUST match the stall \f(CWid\fR." 4
.IX Item "kind 30017 - Stall (addressable). Contains stall name, currency, and shipping zones. The d tag MUST match the stall id."
.PD 0
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 30018\fR \- Product (addressable). Contains product details including price, quantity, and optional specs. The ""d"" tag MUST match the product ""id"". Categories are stored as ""t"" tags." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 30018\fR \- Product (addressable). Contains product details including price, quantity, and optional specs. The \f(CWd\fR tag MUST match the product \f(CWid\fR. Categories are stored as \f(CWt\fR tags." 4
.IX Item "kind 30018 - Product (addressable). Contains product details including price, quantity, and optional specs. The d tag MUST match the product id. Categories are stored as t tags."
.IP "\fBkind 30019\fR \- Marketplace UI/UX (addressable). Customizes the marketplace experience with name, description, theme, and merchant list." 4
.IX Item "kind 30019 - Marketplace UI/UX (addressable). Customizes the marketplace experience with name, description, theme, and merchant list."
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 30020\fR \- Auction (addressable). Similar to products but with ""starting_bid"" and ""duration"" instead of fixed price. The ""d"" tag MUST match the auction ""id""." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 30020\fR \- Auction (addressable). Similar to products but with \f(CWstarting_bid\fR and \f(CWduration\fR instead of fixed price. The \f(CWd\fR tag MUST match the auction \f(CWid\fR." 4
.IX Item "kind 30020 - Auction (addressable). Similar to products but with starting_bid and duration instead of fixed price. The d tag MUST match the auction id."
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 1021\fR \- Bid. Content is the bid amount. References the auction event via an ""e"" tag. Bids reference the event ID (not UUID) so editing an auction after a bid invalidates the bid." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 1021\fR \- Bid. Content is the bid amount. References the auction event via an \f(CWe\fR tag. Bids reference the event ID (not UUID) so editing an auction after a bid invalidates the bid." 4
.IX Item "kind 1021 - Bid. Content is the bid amount. References the auction event via an e tag. Bids reference the event ID (not UUID) so editing an auction after a bid invalidates the bid."
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 1022\fR \- Bid confirmation. Merchant confirms/rejects bids. Status can be ""accepted"", ""rejected"", ""pending"", or ""winner"". References both the bid and auction events via ""e"" tags. May extend the auction duration." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 1022\fR \- Bid confirmation. Merchant confirms/rejects bids. Status can be \f(CWaccepted\fR, \f(CWrejected\fR, \f(CWpending\fR, or \f(CWwinner\fR. References both the bid and auction events via \f(CWe\fR tags. May extend the auction duration." 4
.IX Item "kind 1022 - Bid confirmation. Merchant confirms/rejects bids. Status can be accepted, rejected, pending, or winner. References both the bid and auction events via e tags. May extend the auction duration."
.PD
.PP
Checkout is handled via three message types exchanged as NIP\-04 encrypted
direct messages:
.IP "\fBtype 0\fR \- Customer order with items, shipping zone, and optional contact info." 4
.IX Item "type 0 - Customer order with items, shipping zone, and optional contact info."
.PD 0
.IP "\fBtype 1\fR \- Merchant payment request with payment options (url, btc, ln, lnurl)." 4
.IX Item "type 1 - Merchant payment request with payment options (url, btc, ln, lnurl)."
.IP "\fBtype 2\fR \- Merchant order status update with paid/shipped booleans." 4
.IX Item "type 2 - Merchant order status update with paid/shipped booleans."
.PD
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Marketplace\*(C'\fR object.  Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->new(
\&        name  => \*(AqWidget\*(Aq,
\&        price => 10.50,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS stall_event
.IX Subsection "stall_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->stall_event(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id          => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqMy Stall\*(Aq,
\&        description => \*(AqOptional description\*(Aq,
\&        currency    => \*(AqUSD\*(Aq,
\&        shipping    => [
\&            { id => \*(Aqzone\-1\*(Aq, name => \*(AqUS\*(Aq, cost => 5.0, regions => [\*(AqUS\*(Aq] },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30017 stall Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`currency\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`shipping\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR is optional.
Each shipping zone requires \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`cost\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`regions\*(C'\fR; \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR is
optional.
.SS product_event
.IX Subsection "product_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->product_event(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id          => \*(Aqprod\-1\*(Aq,
\&        stall_id    => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqWidget\*(Aq,
\&        currency    => \*(AqUSD\*(Aq,
\&        price       => 10.50,
\&        quantity    => 100,
\&        description => \*(AqA fine widget\*(Aq,
\&        images      => [\*(Aqhttps://img.jpg\*(Aq],
\&        specs       => [[\*(Aqcolor\*(Aq, \*(Aqblue\*(Aq]],
\&        shipping    => [{ id => \*(Aqzone\-1\*(Aq, cost => 2.0 }],
\&        categories  => [\*(Aqwidgets\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30018 product Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`stall_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`currency\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`price\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`quantity\*(C'\fR
can be \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unlimited items. \f(CW\*(C`categories\*(C'\fR become \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags.
.SS marketplace_event
.IX Subsection "marketplace_event"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->marketplace_event(
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id        => \*(Aqmarket\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name      => \*(AqMy Market\*(Aq,
\&        about     => \*(AqA cool marketplace\*(Aq,
\&        ui        => { theme => \*(Aqdark\*(Aq, darkMode => JSON::true },
\&        merchants => [$pubkey1, $pubkey2],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30019 marketplace UI/UX Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR are required. All other fields are optional.
.SS auction_event
.IX Subsection "auction_event"
.Vb 9
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->auction_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        id           => \*(Aqauction\-1\*(Aq,
\&        stall_id     => \*(Aqstall\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name         => \*(AqRare Item\*(Aq,
\&        starting_bid => 1000,
\&        start_date   => 1700000000,
\&        duration     => 86400,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30020 auction Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`stall_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`starting_bid\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`duration\*(C'\fR are required.
\&\f(CW\*(C`start_date\*(C'\fR is optional; omit if the start date is unknown or hidden.
.SS bid_event
.IX Subsection "bid_event"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->bid_event(
\&        pubkey           => $hex_pubkey,
\&        amount           => 1500,
\&        auction_event_id => $event_id,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1021 bid Net::Nostr::Event. Content is the amount as a
string. An \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag references the auction event.
.SS bid_confirmation_event
.IX Subsection "bid_confirmation_event"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->bid_confirmation_event(
\&        pubkey             => $hex_pubkey,
\&        bid_event_id       => $bid_id,
\&        auction_event_id   => $auction_id,
\&        status             => \*(Aqaccepted\*(Aq,
\&        message            => \*(AqWelcome!\*(Aq,
\&        duration_extended  => 300,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1022 bid confirmation Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`bid_event_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`auction_event_id\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR are required.
\&\f(CW\*(C`message\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`duration_extended\*(C'\fR are optional. Two \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags reference
the bid and auction events.
.SS order_message
.IX Subsection "order_message"
.Vb 9
\&    my $json = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->order_message(
\&        id          => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        items       => [{ product_id => \*(Aqprod\-1\*(Aq, quantity => 2 }],
\&        shipping_id => \*(Aqzone\-1\*(Aq,
\&        name        => \*(AqAlice\*(Aq,
\&        address     => \*(Aq123 Main St\*(Aq,
\&        message     => \*(AqGift wrap please\*(Aq,
\&        contact     => { nostr => $pubkey, phone => \*(Aq+1234567890\*(Aq, email => \*(Aqa@b.com\*(Aq },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds a type 0 order JSON string for NIP\-04 checkout. \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`items\*(C'\fR,
and \f(CW\*(C`shipping_id\*(C'\fR are required. All other fields are optional.
.SS payment_request_message
.IX Subsection "payment_request_message"
.Vb 8
\&    my $json = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->payment_request_message(
\&        id              => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        payment_options => [
\&            { type => \*(Aqln\*(Aq, link => \*(Aqlnbc...\*(Aq },
\&            { type => \*(Aqbtc\*(Aq, link => \*(Aqbc1q...\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&        message => \*(AqPay within 24 hours\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds a type 1 payment request JSON string. \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`payment_options\*(C'\fR
are required. Payment option types include \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`btc\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ln\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`lnurl\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`message\*(C'\fR is optional.
.SS order_status_message
.IX Subsection "order_status_message"
.Vb 6
\&    my $json = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->order_status_message(
\&        id      => \*(Aqorder\-1\*(Aq,
\&        message => \*(AqShipped!\*(Aq,
\&        paid    => JSON::true,
\&        shipped => JSON::true,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds a type 2 order status JSON string. All fields are required.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a marketplace event (kinds 30017, 30018, 30019, 30020, 1021, 1022)
into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Marketplace\*(C'\fR object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized
kinds.
.SS parse_checkout_message
.IX Subsection "parse_checkout_message"
.Vb 3
\&    my $msg = Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->parse_checkout_message($json_string);
\&    say $msg\->checkout_type;  # 0, 1, or 2
\&    say $msg\->order_id;
.Ve
.PP
Parses a checkout JSON string (type 0 order, type 1 payment request, or
type 2 order status) into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Marketplace\*(C'\fR object.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Marketplace\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a marketplace event. Croaks on invalid structure. Addressable
events (30017, 30018, 30019, 30020) must have a \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. Kind 1021 must
have an \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag. Kind 1022 must have two \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
Available on objects returned by "from_event" and "parse_checkout_message".
Which accessors contain data depends on which event kind or message type
was parsed.
.SS stall_id
.IX Subsection "stall_id"
Stall identifier (from kind 30017 or 30018).
.SS product_id
.IX Subsection "product_id"
Product or auction identifier (from kind 30018 or 30020).
.SS name
.IX Subsection "name"
Name of the stall, product, auction, or marketplace.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
Optional description.
.SS currency
.IX Subsection "currency"
Currency code (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`USD\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR).
.SS price
.IX Subsection "price"
Product price (from kind 30018).
.SS quantity
.IX Subsection "quantity"
Available quantity; \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unlimited (from kind 30018).
.SS images
.IX Subsection "images"
Arrayref of image URLs.
.SS specs
.IX Subsection "specs"
Arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`[$key, $value]\*(C'\fR specification pairs.
.SS shipping
.IX Subsection "shipping"
Arrayref of shipping zone hashrefs.
.SS categories
.IX Subsection "categories"
Arrayref of category strings from \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags (kind 30018).
.SS about
.IX Subsection "about"
Marketplace description (kind 30019).
.SS ui
.IX Subsection "ui"
UI configuration hashref (kind 30019).
.SS merchants
.IX Subsection "merchants"
Arrayref of merchant pubkeys (kind 30019).
.SS starting_bid
.IX Subsection "starting_bid"
Starting bid amount (kind 30020).
.SS start_date
.IX Subsection "start_date"
Auction start UNIX timestamp (kind 30020).
.SS duration
.IX Subsection "duration"
Auction duration in seconds (kind 30020).
.SS amount
.IX Subsection "amount"
Bid amount (kind 1021).
.SS auction_event_id
.IX Subsection "auction_event_id"
Referenced auction event ID (kinds 1021, 1022).
.SS bid_event_id
.IX Subsection "bid_event_id"
Referenced bid event ID (kind 1022).
.SS status
.IX Subsection "status"
Bid confirmation status: \f(CW\*(C`accepted\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`rejected\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pending\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`winner\*(C'\fR
(kind 1022).
.SS message
.IX Subsection "message"
Optional message (kinds 1022, checkout messages).
.SS duration_extended
.IX Subsection "duration_extended"
Number of seconds by which the auction is extended (kind 1022).
.SS checkout_type
.IX Subsection "checkout_type"
Checkout message type: 0 (order), 1 (payment request), or 2 (order status).
.SS order_id
.IX Subsection "order_id"
Order identifier (checkout messages).
.SS items
.IX Subsection "items"
Arrayref of item hashrefs with \f(CW\*(C`product_id\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`quantity\*(C'\fR (type 0).
.SS shipping_id
.IX Subsection "shipping_id"
Selected shipping zone ID (type 0).
.SS address
.IX Subsection "address"
Shipping address string (type 0).
.SS contact
.IX Subsection "contact"
Contact hashref with optional \f(CW\*(C`nostr\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`phone\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`email\*(C'\fR (type 0).
.SS payment_options
.IX Subsection "payment_options"
Arrayref of payment option hashrefs with \f(CW\*(C`type\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`link\*(C'\fR (type 1).
.SS paid
.IX Subsection "paid"
Boolean indicating payment received (type 2).
.SS shipped
.IX Subsection "shipped"
Boolean indicating item shipped (type 2).
